<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-02T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="3" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890b.6363 Gulf Oil Corporation/20:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1" type="to">Atherton</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-02T13:00:00-05:00">February 2, 1932—1
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>50. Your despatch 2482, December 29, 1931. If you have not received
                                the reply promised by <persName corresp="#p_OSL1">Oliphant</persName> please take up the matter again informally
                                with the Foreign Office. Explain that the Department does not wish
                                to be unduly insistent in this matter, but since the whole question
                                has been under consideration by the interested departments of the
                                British Government for some time it is hoped that a reply may soon
                                be received.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>